transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service, I can help you.

Speaker 2: Yes, hi.

Speaker 1: I just wanted to check and make sure that I'm not set up—

Speaker 2: For like reoccurring shipments or anything like that.

Speaker 1: Let me pull you up.

Speaker 2: What's your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's Mike Kessner.

Speaker 2: And my birthday, you said?

Speaker 1: Yes, your birthday.

Speaker 2: What else?

Speaker 1: 10-775.

Speaker 2: Okay, you are—

Speaker 1: You want me to pause it so that you're not getting in my—

Speaker 2: Yeah, stop that.

Speaker 1: Actually, I ordered one time, and I did not want the second order.

Speaker 2: I did not sign up for the second one to have it continuously sent to me.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, I paused it so you're not getting any monthlies,

Speaker 1: and you can just call in and place your order whenever you're ready.

Speaker 2: Right, but still, the fact is that you charged me for the second time,

Speaker 1: and I didn't ask for it.

Speaker 2: I didn't set that up.

Speaker 1: Okay, just send it back, and you can be refunded for it.

Speaker 2: You just have to send it back.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Just write return to sender on the package.

Speaker 1: If you open it, it's fine.

Speaker 2: You can tape it up, return to sender.

Speaker 1: Okay, how—wait, but I got to pay for that return?

Speaker 2: No, they'll use the same tag if you just tape it up and send it back.

Speaker 1: But, I mean, is there a cost to it, though, to return?

Speaker 2: No, it'll use the same tracking that it went to you on

Speaker 1: if you returned it in the same packaging.

Speaker 2: Just tape it up.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I don't know how the mail service works.

Speaker 1: It's my knowledge that usually when you send something somewhere,

Speaker 2: that you've got to pay for that.

Speaker 1: That's why I'm asking.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, if you return to sender, it goes on the same postage.

Speaker 2: Okay, got it.

Speaker 1: Okay, that's what I'll do.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
